      • bindColumns

        private void bindColumns()
        Binds the columns in both tables to their appropriate data sources. This method is a series of lambdas that populate the various columns. Lambdas are easy to use here and make the code easy to read because the setCellValueFactory() methods are factories that take an iterated series of constructor methods as input. The alternative would be a series of for loops, which are much more tedious and less readable.

      • displayAppointments

        private void displayAppointments()
        Calls data from the DAO objects and then calls the bind methods to populate the table views with the data.

      • initialize

        public void initialize​(URL url,
                       ResourceBundle rb)
        Initializes the starting conditions of the reports view. The lambda here is a forEach iteration over the key set of a HashMap. The forEach method makes it really easy to read and write functions that iterate over a Collection object.
        Specified by:
        initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
        Parameters:
        url - Unused.
        rb - Unused.
